The fares shown are for information only and are subject to change without notice.
INFORMATION
BAGGAGE Forty (40) pounds of baggage will be carried free on each domestic
ticket, and 66 pounds on each international ticket.
Baggage over this limit is charged
for at the rate per pound of one-half of one percent of the published one-way fare, with
a minimum charge of twenty-five cents (25c).
The liability of the Carrier for loss of or
damage to baggage and/or personal property checked in the Company's care is limited
to the amount of One Hundred Dollars ($100.00) per ticket unless a higher valuation is
declared and paid prior to the departure of the flight.
CANCELLATIONS
—Reservations will not be held on flights from stop-over points
or on return flights originating at points other than where ticket is purchased, unless
passenger secures revalidation from the airline of departure in the city of each departure
at least six hours prior to scheduled flight time.
British Caribhean
Airways may cancel any reservation, if the person holding the
reservation has not presented himself at the airport office of British Caribbean Airways
for the purpose of checking in at least 45 minutes prior to the scheduled departure
time of the flight for which reservation was made.
STOP-OVERS Stop-overs will be permitted at any scheduled stop providing reserva-
tion is made accordingly at beginning of flight.
RESERVATIONS
All reservations must be made in advance and will be held only
long enough to permit purchase of ticket as soon as practicable after reservation on the
originating portion has been confirmed, at which time your specific ticket deadline will
